metadata.description:
“Some lakes run dry, sometimes, while others overflow”

Some Lakes is a love song about meeting my girlfriend, Noémie in Israel. Walking down a crowded beach and swimming in the ocean together, unfazed by all the other people around, only focused on each other.  Swimming so deep into the sunset that all you can see and hear are the waves.

Love is a powerful thing, and when it's present, you see everything in abundance. There’s nothing you can’t do, nothing you can't be.

lyrics.text:
Some lakes

Run dry, sometimes

While others

Overflow

Sun breaks

My eyes open wide

Reminds me

Of your love


When we found love

It was sunset on a crowded beach

But it felt like it was you and me

Ain’t it funny how we

Only see what we need

When we found love

We were deep inside the ocean waves

20 strokes, the land would fade away

Now it’s only us two


Some lakes

Polluted and grimed

While ours stays

Beautiful

Feels familiar and it’s new to me

It’s a deja vu, lucid dreams

Baby your touch is food to me

Gimme that good charcuterie

All we share is evergreen

No where else I'd rather be

Than here, with, you


When we found love

It was sunset on a crowded beach

But it felt like it was you and me

Ain’t it funny how we

Only see what we need

When we found love

We were deep inside the ocean waves

20 strokes, the land would fade away

Now it’s only us two


Swimming in ivory

Sipping out of a wine tree

Might not let it show

Might not let it show

Trying to paint it

But the colors are changing

Might not let it show

Might not let it show

But girl you feel like home
